text:
Queria celebrar un cumpleaños aqui, pero antes quería ir a ver el bar, me dijeron que estarían abiertos el dia de reyes lo cual me pareció raro porque es una fecha importante, no obstante me dijeron que abririan si o si porque el jueves estarian cerrados pero si cambiaban de horario me lo avisaría. Al no avisarme nada, fui como había quedado, a las 10pm el viernes de reyes, y me encuentro con el local cerrado. Igualmente durante esta semana sabiendo lo cerca que estaba el cumple le comenté a la chica, María que quería pagar la reserva de una vez para no perder la disponibilidad incluso sin ver el bar, y ella me dijo que lo fuera a ver y que si alguien tenia intenciones de reservar, me avisaria antes. Pues me encuentro el dia de ayer a las 10pm al frente del bar totalmente cerrado, llamo y me comentan que estan cerrados porque iq abrieron el jueves y ademas me dicen que ya habian reservado el dia que yo queria y que no quedaba sino para finales de enero. Las cosas pasan por algo, esta falta de seriedad me hubiese pasado el dia de la fiesta de cumple y me muero... asi que mejor que me pasó ahora.
Te vende la moto con la simpatía en el telefono y resulta que no es nada seria.
textTranslated:
I wanted to celebrate a birthday here, but first I wanted to go see the bar. They told me they would be open on Three Kings' Day, which seemed odd to me because it's an important holiday. However, they told me they would definitely open because they would be closed on Thursday, but if they changed their hours, they would let me know. Since they didn't let me know, I went as planned, at 10 p.m. on Three Kings' Friday, only to find the bar closed. Also, during this week, knowing how close the birthday was, I told the girl, María, that I wanted to pay for the reservation right away so I wouldn't lose availability even without seeing the bar. She told me to go see it and if anyone wanted to reserve, she would let me know first. Yesterday, at 10 p.m., I found myself in front of the bar, completely closed. I called, and they told me they were closed because they only opened on Thursday. They also told me they had already reserved the day I wanted and that it wasn't until the end of January. Things happen for a reason. This lack of seriousness would have happened to me on my birthday party and I'd have died... so it's better that it happened now.
They sell you the idea by calling you nice, and it turns out they're not serious at all.
